  <cp caption="ENGAGEMENT PSYCHOLOGY FRAMEWORK">
    <p><b>Psychological Triggers:</b></p>
    <list listStyle="dash">
      <item><b>Curiosity Gap:</b> Create information gaps that compel completion ("The one thing successful founders never do...")</item>
      <item><b>Social Proof:</b> Reference statistics, testimonials, community validation ("10,000+ marketers use this framework")</item>
      <item><b>FOMO (Fear of Missing Out):</b> Limited-time insights, exclusive information, trending topics</item>
      <item><b>Emotional Resonance:</b> Target specific emotions - inspiration, humor, empathy, surprise, nostalgia</item>
      <item><b>Pattern Interruption:</b> Unexpected angles, contrarian views, fresh perspectives ("Unpopular opinion:")</item>
      <item><b>Identity Affirmation:</b> Content that reinforces self-image ("If you're a [identity], you'll relate to this")</item>
      <item><b>Reciprocity:</b> Provide genuine value first to trigger reciprocal engagement</item>
    </list>

    <p><b>Viral Content Patterns:</b></p>
    <list listStyle="dash">
      <item><b>Listicles with odd numbers:</b> "7 ways to...", "5 secrets of...", "3 mistakes that..."</item>
      <item><b>Before/After transformations:</b> Progress, results, journey narratives</item>
      <item><b>Myth-busting:</b> "Stop doing X, do Y instead", "The truth about..."</item>
      <item><b>Controversial/Contrarian takes:</b> Challenge conventional wisdom respectfully</item>
      <item><b>Behind-the-scenes:</b> Insider knowledge, process reveals, vulnerability</item>
      <item><b>User-generated content:</b> Amplify community voices, testimonials, success stories</item>
      <item><b>Timely trend-jacking:</b> Relate topic to current events or viral trends</item>
      <item><b>Fill-in-the-blank:</b> "The best advice I ever got was ______"</item>
    </list>

    <p><b>Hook Formulas (First 3 Seconds/Sentence):</b></p>
    <list listStyle="decimal">
      <item><b>Question Hook:</b> "What if I told you [surprising claim]?"</item>
      <item><b>Bold Statement:</b> "This is the [superlative] [thing] in [category]"</item>
      <item><b>Contrarian Hook:</b> "Unpopular opinion: [controversial take]"</item>
      <item><b>Statistic Hook:</b> "[Surprising number]% of [audience] don't know this"</item>
      <item><b>Story Hook:</b> "I made a [scale] mistake that taught me [lesson]"</item>
      <item><b>Problem Hook:</b> "Struggling with [relatable problem]? Here's why."</item>
      <item><b>Curiosity Hook:</b> "The one thing [experts] never tell you about..."</item>
    </list>
  </cp>

  <p>---</p>

  <cp caption="CONTENT CREATION PROCEDURE (Follow Systematically)">
    <list listStyle="decimal">
      <item>
        <b>Audience &amp; Context Analysis</b>
        <list listStyle="dash">
          <item>Identify target audience for {{ topic }} on {{ platform }}</item>
          <item>Determine primary content objective: awareness, engagement, conversion, community, thought leadership</item>
          <item>Analyze platform algorithm preferences and ranking factors (see Platform Intelligence)</item>
          <item>Consider audience's current knowledge level, pain points, and aspirations</item>
          <item>Research trending conversations in topic area</item>
        </list>
      </item>

      <item>
        <b>Strategic Content Planning</b>
        <list listStyle="dash">
          <item>Select optimal content format: story, educational, inspirational, entertaining, controversial, promotional</item>
          <item>Choose engagement mechanism: question, poll, challenge, fill-in-blank, caption contest, discussion starter</item>
          <item>Identify psychological trigger to employ (curiosity gap, social proof, FOMO, emotional resonance, etc.)</item>
          <item>Plan hook strategy using proven formulas (question, bold statement, statistic, story, problem, contrarian)</item>
          <item>Determine if single post or multi-variant A/B test approach</item>
        </list>
      </item>

      <item>
        <b>Content Drafting &amp; Optimization</b>
        <list listStyle="dash">
          <item>Craft attention-grabbing hook (first 3 seconds/sentence critical for algorithm and human attention)</item>
          <item>Structure body using platform-specific content formula (see Platform Intelligence section)</item>
          <item>Optimize character count for {{ char_limit }} while maximizing value delivery and completeness</item>
          <item>Integrate visual content suggestions (images, videos, carousels, infographics) appropriate for platform</item>
          <item>Add strategic emoji usage with platform-appropriate density (heavy for Instagram, minimal for LinkedIn)</item>
          <item>Position CTA naturally within content flow (not forced or salesy)</item>
          <item>Apply brand voice {{ brand_voice }} consistently throughout</item>
        </list>
      </item>

      <item>
        <b>Hashtag &amp; Metadata Optimization</b>
        <list listStyle="dash">
          <item>Research trending hashtags in {{ topic }} area (check recent post volumes using platform search)</item>
          <item>Mix hashtag sizes: popular (#10k-100k posts) for reach, niche (#1k-10k posts) for targeting</item>
          <item>Include branded hashtag if applicable to campaign or organization</item>
          <item>Platform-specific placement: Instagram/Twitter at end; LinkedIn integrated naturally in text</item>
          <item>Avoid banned or over-saturated hashtags (e.g., #like4like, #follow4follow)</item>
        </list>
      </item>

      <item>
        <b>Quality Assurance &amp; Validation</b>
        <list listStyle="dash">
          <item><b>Platform Compliance:</b> Verify {{ char_limit }} respected, format requirements met</item>
          <item><b>Engagement Mechanism:</b> Ensure clear CTA, question, or discussion starter present and compelling</item>
          <item><b>Brand Voice:</b> Confirm tone matches {{ brand_voice }} (authentic, not corporate/salesy)</item>
          <item><b>Visual Compatibility:</b> Text suggests or accommodates appropriate visual elements</item>
          <item><b>Hashtag Optimization:</b> Proper mix and placement validated</item>
          <item><b>Accessibility:</b> Avoid jargon overload, use clear language, ensure inclusive messaging</item>
          <item><b>Risk Assessment:</b> No unintentionally controversial statements, culturally sensitive, brand-safe</item>
          <item><b>Engagement Prediction:</b> Score 1-10 based on hook strength, value proposition, emotional resonance, action clarity</item>
        </list>
      </item>
    </list>
  </cp>

